FIG. 1 is a schematic plan (top) view showing in exploded relation an electrical circuit assembly of individual circuit chips in a planar array which are interconnected by means of ultra-miniature surface-contacting electrical contacts mounted on a substrate and provided in accordance with the present invention;


FIG. 2 is a greatly enlarged schematic side view of an is ultra-miniature card-edge electrical contact (clip) also provided by the invention and showing it making contact to a surface pad on the edge of a circuit chip;


FIG. 3 is a schematic side view of the ultra-miniature card-edge electrical contact of FIG. 2 at one stage of its fabrication in accordance with a method of the present invention;


FIG. 4 is a view similar to FIG. 3 but at a later stage of fabrication of the contact;


FIG. 5 is a view of the electrical contact of FIG. 4 after the contact has been formed into a three-dimensional shape;


FIG. 6 is a view of a partially fabricated electrical contact closely similar to the contact shown in FIG. 5;


FIG. 7 is a view of the electrical contact of FIG. 5 after it has been over-plated with a stiffening metal for strength and resistance to permanent deformation;


FIG. 8 is a greatly enlarged side view of an ultra-miniature surface-contacting electrical contact (such as illustrated in FIG. 1) at one stage of its fabrication in accordance with a method of the present invention;


FIG. 9 is a view similar to FIG. 8 but at a later stage of fabrication of the contact;


FIG. 10 is a view of the electrical contact of FIG. 9 after it has been formed into a three-dimensional shape and over-plated with a stiffening metal for strength and resistance to permanent deformation;


FIG. 11 is a schematic side view of the electrical contact shown in FIG. 10 making initial contact with a surface pad of a circuit chip;


FIG. 12 is a schematic side view of the electrical contact of FIG. 11 after scraping against the surface pad and being pressed into stable, low resistance contact with the pad.


FIG. 13 is an enlarged schematic side view partially broken away of another partially fabricated ultra-miniature surface-contacting electrical connector also embodying features of the invention;


FIG. 14 is a plan (top) view of the connector shown in FIG. 13;


FIG. 15 is a schematic side view of a fully fabricated connector of FIGS. 13 and 14 as it is about to engage a surface pad of a circuit chip; and


FIG. 16 is a similar view showing the connector of FIG. 15 after it has engaged the surface pad of the chip.
